extends javax.swing.JDialog
    SettingsDialog provides a dialog for settings specific to video export and playback.

      • SettingsDialog

        public SettingsDialog​(PreviewFrame parent,
                      double timeFactor,
                      AbstractVideoType type)
        Creates a new SettingsDialog in partially-disabled mode, meaning that only options not pertinent to a specific file will be disabled.
        Parameters:
        parent - Owner container of this dialog.
        timeFactor - The time factor used to control the frame rate.
        type - The currently selected video format

      • SettingsDialog

        public SettingsDialog​(PreviewFrame parent,
                      int originalWidth,
                      int originalHeight,
                      int renderWidth,
                      int renderHeight,
                      double[] times)
        Creates new form Settings dialog in fully enabled mode.
        Parameters:
        parent - Owner container of this dialog.
        originalWidth - The original width of the SVG frames.
        originalHeight - The original height of the SVG frames.
        renderWidth - The current edited width of the SVG frames.
        renderHeight - The current edited height of the SVG frames.
        times - The timestamps of the SVG frames.

      • SettingsDialog

        public SettingsDialog​(PreviewFrame parent,
                      int originalWidth,
                      int originalHeight,
                      int renderWidth,
                      int renderHeight,
                      double[] times,
                      int startTimeIndex,
                      int endTimeIndex,
                      double timeFactor,
                      boolean lockedAspectRatio,
                      AbstractVideoType type)
        Creates new form SettingsDialog in fully enabled mode.
        Parameters:
        parent - Owner container of this dialog.
        originalWidth - The original width of the SVG frames.
        originalHeight - The original height of the SVG frames.
        renderWidth - The current edited width of the SVG frames.
        renderHeight - The current edited height of the SVG frames.
        times - The timestamps of the SVG frames.
        startTimeIndex - The index with which the start time slider begins.
        endTimeIndex - The index with which the end time slider begins.
        timeFactor - The time factor used to control the frame rate.
        lockedAspectRatio - the status flag to determine if the aspect ratio is locked
        type - The currently selected video format
